<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1287799>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Phylogenetic relationships of Hemicycliophora subbotini n. sp. Bayesian 50% majority rule consensus tree as inferred from D2 and D3 expansion segments of 28S rRNA sequence alignment under a transitional of invariable sites with invariable sites and a gamma-shaped distribution model (TIM3 + I + G). Posterior probabilities greater than 0.70 are given for appropriate clades. Newly obtained sequences in this study are shown in bold. Scale bar = expected changes per site." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1287799/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1287801>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Phylogenetic relationships of Hemicycliophora subbotini n. sp. Bayesian 50% majority rule consensus tree as inferred from ITS rRNA sequence alignment under a transitional of invariable sites with invariable sites and a gamma-shaped distribution model (TIM2 + I + G). Posterior probabilities greater than 0.70 are given for appropriate clades. Newly obtained sequences in this study are shown in bold. Scale bar = expected changes per site." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1287801/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

